SIMPLE: swimming
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swimming
<hw>Swim"ming</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That
swims; capable of swimming; adapted to, or used in, swimming; <as>as, a
<ex>swimming</ex> bird; a <ex>swimming</ex> motion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Suffused with moisture; <as>as, <ex>swimming</ex>
eyes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Swimming bell</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
nectocalyx. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Siphonophora</er>.</cd> --
<col><b>Swimming crab</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any one of
numerous species of marine crabs, as those of the family
<fam>Protunidae</fam>, which have some of the joints of one or more
pairs of legs flattened so as to serve as fins.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swimming</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swimming
<hw>Swim"ming</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of one who
swims.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swimming</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Swimming
<hw>Swim"ming</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Swim</er> to be
dizzy.]</ety> <def>Being in a state of vertigo or dizziness; <as>as, a
<ex>swimming</ex> brain</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swimming</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Swimming
<hw>Swim"ming</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Vertigo; dizziness; <as>as, a
<ex>swimming</ex> in the head</as>.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swimmingly</ent>⟦br⟧
